# 📒 My Notebook — Flask Notes App

A full-stack notes management web application built with Python and Flask.

## 🚀 Features
- Create, Read, Update, Delete notes (CRUD)
- SQLite database for persistent storage
- REST API backend with proper HTTP status codes
- Real-time search across titles and content
- Clean dark-themed responsive UI
- Character limit validation on inputs
- Confirmation modal before deleting

## 🛠️ Tech Stack
| Layer    | Technology          |
|----------|---------------------|
| Backend  | Python 3, Flask     |
| Database | SQLite (via sqlite3)|
| Frontend | HTML, CSS, JS (Vanilla) |
| API      | REST (JSON)         |

## 📁 Project Structure
```
notes_app/
├── app.py                  # Flask backend + REST API
├── notes.db                # SQLite database (auto-created)
├── templates/
│   └── index.html          # Frontend UI
└── README.md
```

## ⚙️ How to Run

```bash
# 1. Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/my-notebook.git
cd my-notebook

# 2. Create virtual environment
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate      # Windows
source venv/bin/activate   # Mac/Linux

# 3. Install dependencies
pip install flask

# 4. Run the app
python app.py

# 5. Open in browser
http://127.0.0.1:5000
```

## 🔗 API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint            | Description       |
|--------|---------------------|-------------------|
| GET    | /api/notes          | Get all notes     |
| POST   | /api/notes          | Create a note     |
| GET    | /api/notes/<id>     | Get one note      |
| PUT    | /api/notes/<id>     | Update a note     |
| DELETE | /api/notes/<id>     | Delete a note     |
| GET    | /api/notes/search?q=| Search notes      |

## 📚 What I Learned
- Building REST APIs with Flask
- SQLite database design and queries
- Connecting frontend to backend using fetch()
- HTTP methods and status codes (200, 201, 400, 404, 409)
- CRUD operations end to end